File:Gilardone lotegorisch.png|thumb|right|Title page of Christian Heinrich Gilardone's Lotegorisch book, ''Parodiee, Gedichtches und prousaische Uffsätz. #Vun kaan Jüd’ - vun e Goj'', Speyer, 1835 
Lotegorisch or ''Lottegorisch'' (older own description: ''lochne kodesch'', from the lang-he|laschon = "tongue, language", and ''kodesch'' = "holy") is a trading language and Palatine dialects|Palatine variant of the secret language, Rotwelsch, spoken in the Leiningerland (especially in Carlsberg, Germany|Carlsberg), where in the late 18th century a large number of vagrancy (people)|vagrants, including many Jews, were settled and where many of them worked as itinerant craftsmen and peddlers.<ref name=AM>Meißner (1999)</ref>

